CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 29, 1961, pg. 14, reads: "They'll Do 'Cha-Cha' - A high spot of the Anna B. Heldman Center, April 30, at 4 P.M., will find this trio executing a modern-jazz dancing idiom, the 'Cha-Cha,' during 'Parisian Holiday,' sponsored by the Clover White Club, Mary N. Smith, president. Left to right: Beverly Collins, Charles O'Neil and Joyce Staley. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dancers Beverly Collins, Charles O'Neil and Joyce Staley wearing leotards and wearing and holding straw hats, posed for cha-cha routine at Anna B. Heldman Center
